review_blob: Amazing beer. Very unique thirst quenching hoppiness and a balanced medium body make this exceptional. An array of natural undertones hide just below the delicious wet hop flavor. Really good.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Harvest Wet Hop IPA - Northern Hemisphere

review_blob: A reddish-gold strong ale with little body to hide its 10%. It poured without much head but the aroma was appealing, smoky fruit with soft yeast. The taste showed a thin front of fruit and spice that faded into a rich flavor of smoked fish. The fruit flavors soon collapse to alcohol but its quite drinkable with food. I would only get this again if I craved a lox flavored beer.
